'''开普勒22'''（即'''开普勒22a'''）是[[恒星光谱|G型]][[主序星|主序星]]，距离地球约600[[光年|光年]]。这颗恒星拥有[[行星系统|行星系统]]，第一颗辨认出来的[[系外行星|行星]]位于和地球类似的[[适居带|适居带]]内。开普勒22是一颗[[类太阳恒星|类太阳恒星]]，半径比[[太阳|太阳]]略小，温度比太阳低。<ref>{{cite web |work=Universe Today |title=Kepler Confirms First Planet in Habitable Zone of Sun-Like Star |date=2011-12-05 |url=http://www.universetoday.com/91564/kepler-confirms-first-planet-in-habitable-zone-of-sun-like-star/#more-91564 |access-date=2011-12-06 |archive-date=2012-09-05 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6AS9VGf61?url=http://www.universetoday.com/91564/kepler-confirms-first-planet-in-habitable-zone-of-sun-like-star/#more-91564 |dead-url=no }}</ref> 它位于[[天鹅座|天鹅座]]边界靠近[[天琴座|天琴座]]的地方，[[赤经|赤经]]为19h16m52.2s，[[赤纬|赤纬]]为	+47°53′4.2″。<ref>{{cite web |title=Kepler Discoveries |date=2011-12-05 |url=http://kepler.nasa.gov/Mission/discoveries/ |access-date=2011-12-06 |archive-date=2017-04-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170401080610/https://kepler.nasa.gov/MIssion/discoveries/ |dead-url=yes }}</ref>

==行星系统==
2011年12月5日，科学家宣布在开普勒22的可居住带内发现一颗类似地球的[[系外行星|系外行星]][[开卜勒22b|开卜勒22b]]。<ref name="popsci">{{cite web | url=http://www.popsci.com/science/article/2011-12/kepler-team-confirms-first-earth-planet-habitable-zone-and-finds-1094-more-worlds | title=Kepler Team Confirms First Earth-like Planet in a Habitable Zone, And Finds 1,094 More Worlds | work=Popular Science | date=December 5, 2011 | accessdate=December 5, 2011 | author=Boyle, Rebecca | archive-date=2012-09-05 | archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6AS9VxREL?url=http://www.popsci.com/science/article/2011-12/kepler-team-confirms-first-earth-planet-habitable-zone-and-finds-1094-more-worlds | dead-url=no }}</ref>这是[[克卜勒太空望远镜|克卜勒太空望远镜]]第一颗确认肯定存在的位于恒星[[适居带|适居带]]内的系外行星。<ref>{{cite web |work=Space.com |title=NASA Telescope Confirms Alien Planet in Habitable Zone |date=2011-12-05 |url=http://www.space.com/13821-nasa-kepler-alien-planets-habitable-zone.html |access-date=2011-12-06 |archive-date=2017-06-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170605001402/http://www.space.com/13821-nasa-kepler-alien-planets-habitable-zone.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

